    "recap_headline": "North Carolina State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "RALEIGH, N.C. \u2013\nAfter the Wolfpack scored two runs in the bottom of the seventh to take a 5-4 lead, Boston College responded with an eight-run eighth inning to even the series and beat NC State 12-5 Saturday afternoon at Doak Field.\nWith the Wolfpack (15-4, 1-1) trailing 4-3,\nDrew Lanphere\nled off the bottom of the seventh with his second home run of the season, tying the game at 4-4. Ret Johnson, who went 3-for-3, singled and reached third after a\nChris McHugh\nsingle and a\nDalton Bargo\nflyout. Shortstop\nMikey Ryan\nwent 3-for-5, including an 11-pitch at-bat that ended with a single through the left side, giving the Wolfpack its first lead of the game.\nThe lead was short-lived as Boston College (11-7, 3-2) loaded the bases with nobody out in the top of the eighth. An error allowed the tying run to score, and a wild pitch gave the Eagles the lead. Three more runs scored after a triple, and another three after a home run. The Wolfpack pitchers walked four in the frame, and six of the eight runs were unearned.\nThis was the first loss of the season for the Pack when having the lead after seven innings.\nJacob Dudan\npitched seven innings, allowing four runs on seven hits, with just one walk and seven strikeouts.\nLuke Hemric\ntook over from Dudan but faced only one batter after issuing a walk.\nCollins Black\n(2-1) came in and was credited with the loss.\nA home run by Boston College in the first inning gave the Eagles an early lead. It was the first home run Dudan had allowed all season.\nNC State took the lead shortly after, scoring three runs in the second inning. Sacrifice flies from\nSherman Johnson\nand\nBrayden Fraasman\nbrought in the first two runs. Three consecutive singles followed, capped by\nTy Head\n, who scored Lanphere from second to make it 3-1.\nA walk, a hit-by-pitch, and three singles scored three more runs for the visitors to take a 4-3 lead in the top of the fourth.\nDudan then retired 10 straight batters from the fourth through the sixth innings.\nThe series wraps up on Sunday, March 15th, at 12 p.m., as the Pack aims for its first ACC series win of the season at Doak Field."
  },
